title: Four Pakistanis hurt by Yemeni shelling in Saudi Arabia
text:
Four Pakistanis hurt by Yemeni shelling in Saudi Arabia Web Report /Najran Filed on February 22, 2017 Share 
Reuters file photo The injured expatriates were taken to a nearby hospital Four Pakistani nationals were injured by military projectiles fired from Yemen by Houthi militias in the southern Najran region, the Saudi Press Agency (SPA) reported. The report quoted Capt. Abdullah Al-Farie, acting spokesman of Civil Defense in Najran, as saying that the projectiles targeted Najran city. The injured expatriates were taken to a nearby hospital, he said. Share
